  <style>@charset "UTF-8";:root{--tier-white-bg:white;--tier-yellow-bg:yellow;--tier-orange-bg:orangered;--tier-brown-bg:brown;--tier-red-bg:red;--tier-purple-bg:purple;--tier-green-bg:green;--tier-blue-bg:blue;--tier-cyan-bg:cyan;--tier-grey-bg:grey;--tier-pink-bg:pink;--tier-white-color:white;--tier-yellow-color:yellow;--tier-orange-color:rgb(238, 142, 39);--tier-brown-color:rgb(173, 72, 5);--tier-red-color:rgb(238, 42, 42);--tier-purple-color:rgb(187, 59, 187);--tier-green-color:green;--tier-blue-color:blue;--tier-cyan-color:cyan;--tier-grey-color:grey;--tier-pink-color:pink;--tier-visible-color:rgb(200, 200, 200);--tier-hidden-color:rgba(200, 200, 200, .5);--unique-item-color:rgb(175, 96, 37);--currency-color:rgb(170,158,130);--normal-item-color:rgb(200,200,200);--magic-item-color:rgb(136,136,255);--rare-item-color:rgb(255,255,119);--quest-item-color:rgb(74, 230, 58);--divination-card-color:rgb(14, 186, 255);--corrupted-color:rgb(210, 0, 0);--gem-color:rgb(27,162,155);--enchantment-color:rgb(184, 218, 241);--fire-color:rgb(150,0,0);--cold-color:rgb(54,100,146);--lightning-color:rgb(255,215,0);--chaos-color:rgb(208,32,144);--unidentified-color:rgb(208, 91, 91);--property-color:rgb(127, 127, 127);--property-value-color:rgb(200, 200, 200);--light-color:#e2e2e2}h2,h3{color:var(--light-color);font-family:FontinSmallcaps,sans-serif;font-weight:400}ul,ol{display:block;list-style-type:"- ";padding:0 0 0 24px;margin:0 0 10px}ol{list-style-type:decimal}li{display:list-item}ol ul{list-style-type:circle;margin-left:16px}ol ol{list-style-type:lower-latin;margin-left:16px}a[target=_blank]:not(.no-icon):after{content:"\ea7e";display:inline-block;font-family:icomoon!important;margin-left:4px;font-size:90%;opacity:.8}a[target=_blank]:not(.no-icon):hover:after{opacity:1}.container-fluid,.container-fluid .content{min-width:512px}:root{--unique-item-color:rgb(240,105,22);--magic-item-color:rgb(122,151,254);--rare-item-color:rgb(254,224,85)}</style><link rel="stylesheet" href="styles-FIPDMAD2.css" media="print" onload="this.media='all'"><noscript><link rel="stylesheet" href="styles-FIPDMAD2.css"></noscript></head>
  <body class="modern trade en_US">
    <script>
      const assetBaseUrl = location.hostname === 'localhost' ? '' : 'https://static.poe2filter.com';
      // Must match bg key in SettingsService (`{prefix}-bg-image-040`)
      const bg = (localStorage.getItem('poe-bg-image-050') || 'aldur-rune2') + '.webp';
      if (bg != 'zen.webp') {
        document.body.style.backgroundImage = `url('${assetBaseUrl}/img/bg/${bg}')`;
      } else {
        document.body.style.backgroundImage = 'none';
        document.body.style.backgroundColor = '#000';
      }
    </script>

    <div class="container-fluid full" id="app">
      <div class="content">

      <div class="wrapper">
        <!-- <div id="statusBar">
          <div class="statusBarCenter"></div>
          <div class="statusBarRight"></div>
        </div> -->
        <div class="logo">
          <a href="https://poe2filter.com">
            <img src="/logo-filter.webp">
          </a>
        </div>

        <app-root>
          <div class="loading-placeholder">
            <span class="loading-text">Loading...</span>
          </div>
        </app-root>

        <div class="results block">
          <div class="row row-total row-justify-content-left">
            <div class="info">
              <h2 class="info-title text-align-center bigger gradient-title">Examples</h2>

              <div class="examples">
                <div class="example text-align-center">
                  <img src="https://static.poe2filter.com/img/examples/leveling-gear.webp" class="example-image">
                </div>
                <div class="example text-align-center">
                  <img src="https://static.poe2filter.com/img/examples/currency.webp" class="example-image">
                </div>
                <div class="example text-align-center">
                  <img src="https://static.poe2filter.com/img/examples/uniques.webp" class="example-image">
                </div>
              </div>

            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="results block">
          <div class="row row-total row-justify-content-left">
            <div class="info">
              <h2 class="info-title bigger text-align-center gradient-title">Filter Philosophy</h2>

              <div class="principles">
                <div class="principle">
                  <h3 class="info-title">Minimalist Style</h3>

                  <p>
                    Path of Exile has <strong>beautiful graphics and a dark atmosphere</strong>. Its item color theme nostalgically goes back all the way to Diablo 2. We'd hate to spoil that by adding many different out-of-theme colors and fonts. This filter stays close to the 'default' label styles. We only add highlight beams in self-explanatory colors: white, yellow, orange, red and purple for top-tier items. Highlighted items are shown on the minimap too.
                  </p>
                </div>

                <div class="principle">
                  <h3 class="info-title">Remove Clutter</h3>

                  <p>
                    Halfway through the campaign, many items start dropping, most of which you won't be interested in for your character: Normal and Magic items, Weapons not usable by your build, and Armour which doesn't have the right defences. <strong>This filter hides them</strong>, always keeping a clean overview and adding to the game's beautiful atmosphere.
                  </p>
                </div>

                <div class="principle">
                  <h3 class="info-title">Enhance Efficiency</h3>

                  <p>
                    Using both the tiered color highlights and the minimap icons, you'll never miss any important item. <strong>The higher the tier, the more likely you will want to pick it up</strong>, even backtracing a bit.
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>

              <div class="principles">
                <div class="principle">
                  <h3 class="info-title">Easy to use</h3>

                  <p>
                    Going with <strong>the presets is just fine for most people</strong>, but it's <strong>easy to adapt</strong> it to your preferences on the Quick Filters and Tier List pages.
                  </p>

                  <h3 class="info-title">Nothing to learn</h3>

                  <p>You <strong>don't have to learn</strong> what different <strong>colors or styles mean</strong>: the Drop Tier system is self-exaplanatory. Higher Drop Tier means more valuable.

                </p></div>

                <div class="principle">
                  <h3 class="info-title">Market-value Drop Tiers</h3>

                  <p>
                    Currency and unique items can be more or less rare -- that is, they have a <strong>higher or lower market value</strong> -- a product of their utility divided by their drop chance. We call these <strong>Drop Tiers</strong>, white through red (or purple if you're really lucky). All drops are highlighted using an appropriate beam and icon on the minimap. Classifying items into these Drop Tiers is <strong>based on their value on the in-game Currency Exchange</strong>. Currency values are automatically updated every 4 hours, Uniques values once per day.
                  </p>

                  <p>
                    However, you can always move currency or Uniques to a different Drop Tier, or hide them entirely. It's as easy as dragging and dropping the item to the desired tier.
                  </p>
                </div>

                <div class="principle">
                  <h3 class="info-title">Safety first</h3>

                  <p>
                    Any change to this filter is <strong>tested beforehand</strong>, and gets a test-run. All <strong>item names are always exact matches</strong> from https://poe2db.tw, which is actual data-mined from the game client, avoiding typos.
                  </p>

                  <p>
                    Using the 'Sync' functionality is as safe as it gets. You authenticate on pathofexile.com, only allowing the tool access to most basic account information and the ability to save filters. We're using all <a href="https://www.pathofexile.com/developer/docs/authorization" target="_blank">GGG's API Developer requirements</a>, which in turn follow the <strong>industry's security best practices</strong> such as using <a href="https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/rfc6749" target="_blank">OAuth2 Authorization code flow</a> with <a href="https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/rfc7636" target="_blank">PKCE</a>.
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>

            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="results block">
          <div class="row row-total row-justify-content-left">
            <div class="info">
              <h2 class="info-title bigger text-align-center gradient-title" id="how-to-use-this-website">How To Use This Website</h2>
              <h3 class="info-title">Creating your first filter</h3>
              <ol>
                <li>Choose one of the <a href="/presets">Presets</a>, and/or use the <a href="/quick-filters">Quick Filters</a> and the other tabs to adjust the filter to your preferences. The Quick Filter tab contains a tutorial to guide you around.</li>
                <li>
                  Once you're done, you have two options:
                  <ul>
                    <li><strong>Log in</strong> to pathofexile.com, and then <strong>Sync</strong> the filter directly to the game. It will be created as <strong>poe2filter</strong> in cyan. This is the only option for Console and GeForce Now players.</li>
                    <li>Alternatively, on PC use <strong>Save to new file</strong> (Firefox: <strong>Download</strong>) to save the filter directly into your game folder: <span class="code">%userprofile%\Documents\My Games\Path of Exile 2</span>.
                      You can open the correct folder from the Game's Settings Menu under 'Game'.
                      <br><span class="extra-info">Pro tip: In Windows, you can 'pin' a folder for easy access in your Windows Explorer. Just right-lick the folder and select 'Pin to Quick Access'.</span></li>
                  </ul>
                </li>
                <li>In the game, <strong>select</strong> the filter from the dropdown menu in the 'Game' Settings Menu. The game will save it for future use, and load it on startup.</li>
                <li>This website will <strong>store</strong> your filters in the browser. As long as you use the same browser, you can always continue to edit your already stored filters.</li>
              </ol>

              <h3 class="info-title">Updating a filter</h3>
              <ol>
                <li>Make the desired <strong>changes</strong> to your filter. Once finished, you have three options:
                  <ol>
                    <li>If necessary first <strong>Log in</strong> again, and <strong>Sync</strong> your updated filter. This is the only option for console and GeForce Now players.</li>
                    <li>Click <strong>Save to file</strong> to overwrite the linked file directly. On Firefox, re-<strong>Download</strong> and replace the existing file — make sure the name is still correct, as your browser may append (1).</li>
                    <li>Alternatively, copy the filter text using the '<strong>Copy to Clipboard</strong>' button, and paste it directly in your filter file which is already in the game folder.
                      <br><span class="extra-info">Pro Tip: You can just keep your filter file always open in the background while playing the game.</span></li>
                  </ol>
                </li>
                <li>In the game, click the '<strong>Refresh</strong>' button next to the filter under 'Game' settings.</li>
                <li>The game will tell you when the filter was loaded correctly (or if it encountered a parsing error).</li>
              </ol>

              <h3 class="info-title">Creating other filters</h3>
              <p>You can create a different filter for each of your characters, for different stages of the game, or both. You can start from scratch, or start by cloning an existing filter.</p>
              <ol>
                <li>In the top-right-hand corner of the page, you can see your currently active filter. The default filter is called 'poe2filter'. Clicking (Change) will open the Filter Selector dialog.</li>
                <li>This dialog has three sections: Stored Filters, Account Filters, and Other Filters.
                  <ol>
                    <li>The 'Stored Filters' section lists all filters stored on this browser, which are immediately available to edit and use. Here you can also rename a filter by clicking on its name and entering a new (unique) name.</li>
                    <li>If you are logged in, the 'Account Filters' will display all other filters that were created with poe2filter.com which are stored on your pathofexile.com account, but not yet stored on your browser. The only thing you can do with those is download (<span class="icon icon-download"></span>) them to your browser. Then you can start editing them.
                      <br>Note: If you are not yet logged in to pathofexile.com, the dialog will display a link to do so.</li>
                    <li>If you have any filters stored on your pathofexile.com account which were not created with poe2filter.com, they are displayed purely for your information in the 'Other Filters' section.</li>
                  </ol>
                </li>
                <li>
                  To create a new filter, click the 'Create New' button to create one with the default settings, or click the Clone (<span class="icon icon-copy"></span>) button next to an existing filter stored on the browser. Be sure to change the name.
                </li>
                <li>
                  You can switch between filters at any time by clicking on the row.
                </li>
                <li>
                  You can remove filters from your browser's storage (<span class="icon icon-bin"></span>). Note that if you have syncronized them to your pathofexile.com account, they will still continue to exist there. It is not possible to delete filters from your account through GGG's API's. To delete a filter from your account, you must navigate to your pathofexile.com account's filters page.
                </li>
                <li>
                  Lastly, from the Filter Selector dialog, you can synchronize (<span class="icon icon-upload"></span>) your stored filters to your pathofexile.com account. This does the same thing as using the 'Sync to PoE2' button on the filter tool.
                </li>
              </ol>

              <h3 class="info-title">Importing a .filter file</h3>
              <p>You can import any .filter file that was generated with this website -- your own, but also other players'!</p>
              <ol>
                <li>Ideally, if you use a downloaded filter, first place it in the game's filters folder.</li>
                <li>On this website, click the '<strong>Import</strong>' button left of the 'Download' and 'Copy to Clipboard' buttons.</li>
                <li>If necessary, browse to the filter's location. <strong>Open</strong> the filter.</li>
                <li>Make any necessary <strong>adjustments</strong>. If you're importing another player's filter, be sure to double-check all the Quick Filter settings!</li>
                <li>If you only want to import styles from a filter (also called a 'Skin') or another section such as Quick Filters, use the '<strong>Custom Import</strong>' feature instead of the regular 'Quick Import'. You can find the 'Custom Import' feature under the small down-arrow next to the Import button.</li>
                <li>Continue as you would normally.</li>
              </ol>

              <h3 class="info-title">Filter Syntax</h3>
              <p>
                For more information and a thorough guide on the Path Of Exile and Path Of Exile 2 Item Filter options and syntax,
                check out the <a href="https://www.pathofexile.com/item-filter/about" target="_blank"><strong>official page</strong></a>
                and/or this <a href="https://www.poewiki.net/wiki/Guide:Item_filter_guide" target="_blank"><strong>wiki page</strong></a>.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="results block">
          <div class="row row-total row-justify-content-left display-block">
            <div class="info">
              <h2 class="info-title bigger text-align-center gradient-title">Feedback & support</h2>
              <p class="text-align-center">
                <strong>Before reporting an issue</strong>, please make sure your filter is successfully loaded in the game.
                You can also CTRL+C the item's details in-game, and CTRL+V them anywhere in the tool. This will tell you which rule(s) are affecting the item, if any.
              </p>
              <p class="text-align-center">
                <strong>Feedback and bugreports</strong> are welcome at the <strong><a href="https://www.pathofexile.com/forum/view-thread/3630063" target="_blank">PoE Forum Thread</a></strong> or on our <strong><a href="https://discord.gg/JbaMnwngvq" target="_blank">Discord</a></strong>.
                When reporting an issue, please download and include your .filter file, and when relevant, copy/paste the item's details. That makes it much easier for us to help you!
              </p>
              <p class="text-align-center">
                I'm making and updating this website in my spare time. You can <strong>support</strong> me by <strong><a href="https://buymeacoffee.com/poe2filter" target="_blank" class="no-icon"><span class="icon icon-buymeacoffee"></span> buying me a coffee</a></strong>
                or by <strong><a href="https://patreon.com/poe2filter" target="_blank" class="no-icon"><span class="icon icon-patreon-icon"></span> becoming a patron</a></strong>!
                But more importantly, if you like this filter & website, don't forget to <strong>spread the word</strong> on social/gaming media!
              </p>

              <p class="text-align-center">
                <img src="/img/logo-poe1-small.webp">
                <br><br>Looking for a <strong>Path of Exile 1</strong> filter?
                Visit <a href="https://poe1filter.com">poe1filter.com</a> instead.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="results block last-block">
          <div class="row row-total row-justify-content-left display-block">
            <div class="info">
              <h2 class="info-title bigger text-align-center gradient-title">What People Are Saying</h2>
              <div class="praises">
                <div class="praise">
                  <span class="praise-text">
                    I really like all the improvements you've done since the PoE1 release and I'm glad it's not just a pretty husk, but becoming an absolutely awesome tool. [...] Your ID-mod parsing work is masterful! Huge recommendations for anyone who wants a great vanilla-looking filter with good customization options
                  </span>
